# Mushajjir — .clinerules
# This file is read by Cline/Codex agents on every session.
# It documents project conventions, available tooling, and recurring patterns.

## Project overview
- Vue 3 + Vite frontend app
- Pinia for state management
- Vue Flow for canvas/graph rendering
- No backend — everything runs in the browser (localStorage)

## Available scripts (package.json)
- `npm run dev` — start Vite dev server on http://localhost:5173
- `npm run build` — production build
- `npm run preview` — preview production build

## Utility scripts (scripts/)
- `bash scripts/check-build.sh` — runs `vite build` and reports success/failure
- `bash scripts/create-pr.sh BRANCH "TITLE" [body-file]` — stage, commit, push, create PR

## Git workflow
- Branch naming: `type/optional-scope-description` (e.g., `feat/api-endpoints`, `fix/canvas-crash`, `chore/deps-update`)
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `style`
- PRs target `main`
- Worktrees: use `git checkout -b branch-name` from detached HEAD

## Before committing / pushing
1. Run `bash scripts/check-build.sh` to verify the build passes
2. Stage all changes with `git add -A`
3. Commit with a conventional commit message
4. Push and create PR via `bash scripts/create-pr.sh` or manually

## Code conventions
- Vue: Single File Components with `<script setup>` and `<style scoped>`
- State: Pinia stores in `src/stores/`, services in `src/services/`
- New components go in `src/components/`
- Use `<Teleport to="body">` for modals/overlays
- For large new files (>6000 chars), use `write_file` tool instead of `editor` + `insert_line` to avoid line-count drift
- After creating/editing a `.vue` file, verify structure with:
  `grep -n "</template>|<script|<style>" src/components/YourFile.vue`

## Environment notes
- `dist/` and `node_modules/` may be symlinks to `/srv/dev/🌳 Mushajjir/` in worktree setups
- If symlinks are missing, create them:
  `ln -s /srv/dev/🌳 Mushajjir/dist dist`
  `ln -s /srv/dev/🌳 Mushajjir/node_modules node_modules`
- No special `.env` required for development
